# Git Commit Author

Always commit as **Iman Suherman** with email **iman.suherman@gmail.com**.

- Pass `--author` on every commit. Do not rely on git config (global config may be `suherman@qantas.com.au`).
- Format: `--author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>"`
- If amending a commit, always include the same `--author` flag.

```bash
git commit --author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>" -m "MVKS-168: Short description of the change."
git log -1 --format="%an <%ae>"
```

After committing, verify the author is `Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>`. If wrong, amend immediately:

```bash
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Iman Suherman" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="iman.suherman@gmail.com" \
  git commit --amend --author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>" --no-edit
```

## Local git hooks (repo setup)

Install both hooks if missing. They enforce author and strip Cursor co-author lines even when `--author` is forgotten.

**`.git/hooks/post-commit`** — auto-corrects wrong author or committer, then asynchronously checks ct-mcp plugin commits for release. Install from version-controlled hooks:

```bash
npm run install-hooks
```

Source: `githooks/post-commit`. After author/committer correction, plugin-only commits trigger `scripts/post-commit-release.cjs` in the background (logs to `.git/post-commit-release.log`). Set `CT_MCP_POST_COMMIT_RELEASE=0` to disable.

**`.git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg`** — strips Cursor co-author trailers:

```bash
cat > .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash
sed -i '' '/[Cc]o-authored-by:.*[Cc]ursor/d' "$1"
sed -i '' '/cursoragent@cursor\.com/d' "$1"
EOF
chmod +x .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg
```
